<BaseLayout language="en" title="Privacy Policy — AMULET" description="How Amulet stores journal content, uses private iCloud sync, and handles anonymous analytics, crash reports and purchases." canonicalPath="/privacy/" bodyClass="legal-page">
<main><p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">AMULET · TAROT JOURNAL</a></p><h1>Privacy Policy</h1><p class="updated">Last updated: July 15, 2026</p><p class="lede">Amulet is built so that your cards stay yours.</p>
<h2>What we store, and where</h2><p>Everything you create in Amulet — spreads, questions, notes, photos, your card of the day, your practice settings — is stored locally on your device and, if you use iCloud, synced through your own private iCloud account. We do not operate servers and cannot read, access, or recover your content.</p>
<h2>The AI reads on-device too</h2><p>Thread readings are generated by Apple Intelligence directly on your device. Nothing you write, ask, or pull is sent anywhere to be processed.</p>
<h2>What we collect</h2><ul><li><strong>Anonymous usage analytics</strong> (TelemetryDeck): anonymized signals such as “spread saved” or “onboarding completed”, used to understand which features matter. TelemetryDeck never receives your name, email, journal entries, cards, questions, notes, or photos, and cannot identify you. See <a href="https://telemetrydeck.com/privacy">telemetrydeck.com/privacy</a>.</li><li><strong>Crash reports</strong> (Firebase Crashlytics): technical information about an app failure, such as the device model, operating-system version and crash trace, used only to diagnose and fix errors. Never the content you create.</li><li><strong>Purchases</strong> (Apple and RevenueCat): Apple processes your one-time purchase. RevenueCat receives an anonymous app-user identifier and purchase metadata to validate your access. We never see your payment details. See <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy/">revenuecat.com/privacy</a>.</li></ul>
<h2>Photos and camera</h2><p>Photos you attach to a spread are saved into your journal only — on your device and in your private iCloud. Camera access is used solely to take that photo, at your request.</p><h2>Notifications</h2><p>Daily reminders are scheduled locally on your device. There are no push servers.</p><h2>What we don’t do</h2><ul><li>No accounts. No email collection. No ads. No tracking across apps.</li><li>We never sell data. There is no data to sell.</li></ul><h2>Your rights</h2><p>Delete the app and your local data is gone. Manage or delete iCloud data in Settings → Apple ID → iCloud. For anything else, write to <a href="mailto:esthersarasua.dev@gmail.com">esthersarasua.dev@gmail.com</a>.</p><h2>Changes</h2><p>If our practices change, we will update this page and the “Last updated” date above.</p></main>
